                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270111-167-off926 t18270111-167-crimeloc929"></join>. On the 4th of December, I went to see a friend in Belton-street; I heard several children making a noise in the shop or parlour - I opened the door and said to a woman, "I wonder you have all this noise," and told them to leave the room - the prisoner was there, and said he would not; I took hold of him to put him out; some others went out with him - I shut the door after him, and then missed my shawl off my shoulder; it must have been snatched, but I do not know who by - the prisoner put the light out, or I should have seen who took it; it has not been found.</p>
